from solution import Solution

def run_tests():
    sol = Solution()
    tests = [
        ("2523533", "23"),
        ("221", "21"),
        ("22", ""),
        ("12", "12"),  # 1 appears once, 2 appears once -> but 2 must appear 2 times, so invalid -> actually should be ""
        ("112222", "12"), # 1 appears twice -> invalid, so none
        ("1223334444", "23"),
    ]
    # Adjusted expected outputs for correctness
    tests = [
        ("2523533", "23"),
        ("221", "21"),
        ("22", ""),
        ("12", ""),
        ("112222", ""),
        ("1223334444", "34"),
    ]

    for i, (s, expected) in enumerate(tests):
        out = sol.findValidPair(s)
        print(i, s, out, expected, "OK" if out == expected else "FAIL")

if __name__ == '__main__':
    run_tests()

        ("22", ""),
